column1: #Text=East Coast and Midlands is a region of Ireland .
#Text=( Baile Átha Cliath , Town of the Hurdled Ford ) – Dublin is the capital of Ireland and has population of over 1.6m in the Greater Dublin Area
#Text=The main access points when it comes to getting into Leinster are by road , sea and air .
#Text=Traditionally Leinster has both been the most developed area in Ireland and the most populous area in Ireland .
#Text=As a result the road infrastructure in Leinster is very good as it radiates out from Dublin .

#Text=While there are other airports in Leinster which do cater for international flights , ( Baldonnel Casement Aerodrome and Weston Executive Airport ) , the only International airport is Dublin Airport ( DUB ) .
#Text=Leinster is served by Dublin Port ( serving Liverpool and Holyhead ) , Dun Laoghaire ( serving Holyhead ) and Rosslare Europort ( serving Fishguard and Pembroke ) .

#Text=While the rail services in Ireland are not at the level of other European countries , things are improving in terms of station upgrades , investment in rolling stock and the amount of trains run daily .
#Text=In Leinster there are four main lines operated daily by Irish Rail :
#Text=Dublin to Cork ( serving Portlaoise , Thurles , Mallow )
#Text=Travelling by car around the East Coast and Midlands of Ireland is not the arduous task that it was even five years ago .
#Text=The road infrastructure is the subject of continuous improvement as many of the main arteries connecting Dublin to the rest of Ireland are upgraded to motorway standard .
#Text=The road network in Ireland radiates outwards from Dublin City and the M50 ring road from the N1 to Belfast to the N11 to Wexford .
#Text=N3 - Dublin to Ballyshannon ( serving Monaghan , Cavan and Enniskillen )
#Text=M7 / N7 - Dublin to Limerick ( serving Portlaoise , Cashel , Mitchelstown ) and M8 / N8 to Cork

#Text=Car rental in the East Coast and Midlands area is mainly confined to Dublin Airport and Dublin City although some car rental companies have locations at Dun Laoghaire Port and Rosslare Europort .
#Text=While all car rental companies in Ireland have rental desks in the arrivals hall of Dublin Airport , the list of car rental companies with inner city locations is far less .
#Text=Some of the car rental companies will advertise city centre locations , but these locations are mostly only drop-offs for which an additional charge will added .
#Text=The locations are accessible by the DART which is a regular commuter train service covering most of the coastline north and south of Dublin .
#Text=Mulhuddart - do n't miss this thrilling outpost of civil society ; challenging conversation guaranteed
#Text=Dalkey village/town is listed as an Irish heritage town and as such has a rich history , with no less than three castles within the town borders , making it a great day trip from the city .
#Text=Climb Killiney Hill and see the stunning views out around the bay and to Dalkey Island .
#Text=Walk along the strand , visit the famed Blackrock market , a flea market open on weekends and bank holidays , and have a drink at O'Rourke 's , the old haunt of the Irish author Flann O'Brien .
#Text=Serviced by the DART and the 4 , 4A , 5 , 45 , 7 , and 8 buses .
#Text=Climb Bray Head , or walk on its sea front esplanade .
#Text=The Irish National Stud ( outside Kildare Town located adjacent to The Japanese Gardens ) .
#Text=This is a working thoroughbred horse farm .
#Text=Large gothic castle , said to be haunted .
#Text=Durrow Abbey remains a largely undisturbed early historic and medieval monastic site containing a complex of archaeological monuments , ecclesiastical and secular , visible and sub-surface .
#Text=The Christian monastic site of Clonmacnoise in Offaly displays large round towers and beautifully decorated high crosses .
#Text=Temple Bar is a bit of a tourist trap but it does have some nice things to see .
#Text=Home to the five Irish Classic Horse Races .
#Text=A steeplechase race track and home to the four-day Punchestown Festival in late April .
#Text=Open to the public for tours during the summer , serves food and is also a concert venue , with organic farmers market at weekends .
#Text=There are some excellent golf courses in the East Coast and Midlands : The K Club ( which hosted the 2006 Ryder Cup ) , Carton House , Castlewarden , and Tullamore Golf Club .
#Text=The first meeting held at Fairyhouse was in 1848 when the Ward Union hunt held their point-to-point at this venue .
#Text=From these small beginnings Fairyhouse quickly established itself as one of Ireland 's premier racecourses .
#Text=In 1870 the Irish Grand National was run for the first time and the winner was ‘ Sir Robert Peel ' .

#Text=The Grand National quickly became Ireland 's most valuable and prestigious steeplechase and each success has its own rich tale , none more amazing than the win in 1929 of a six year old mare ‘ Alike ' , owned and ridden by 5'4 ” Frank Wise who was missing three fingers and who rode with a wooden leg .
#Text=Fairyhouse has always been one of the finest and fairest racecourses and continues to attract the leading horses both on the flat and over jumps .

#Text=Arkle , Desert Orchid , Flying Bolt , Captain Christy , Prince Regent , Persian War , L'escargot and more recently Istabraq , Bobbyjo , Florida Pearl and Limestone Lad are just some of the legendary greats that have graced the almost 2-mile circuit .

#Text=There are sculptures made by many different people scattered around the parkland .
